00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:20,321
Alleged ties.

501
00:37:21,865 --> 00:37:24,284
And I suggest you keep
that draft to yourself.

502
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:28,455
The DOJ's not going to topple
a government, Agent Peña.

503
00:37:31,499 --> 00:37:33,219
You can't tell me you're
surprised by that.

504
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:39,382
Some part of me was holding
out hope, I guess.

505
00:37:41,009 --> 00:37:43,089
Well, you should tell that
part to grow the fuck up.

506
00:37:44,637 --> 00:37:47,807
No, I mean it, Agent Peña.
You should be happy.

507
00:37:47,891 --> 00:37:49,976
You played the system
like a goddamn fiddle.

508
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:54,314
[CHUCKLES]

509
00:37:54,773 --> 00:37:55,815
You won.

510
00:38:03,823 --> 00:38:05,033
Yes, sir.

511
00:38:16,169 --> 00:38:17,587
[PEÑA] Another deal.

512
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:21,216
A compromise.

513
00:38:23,551 --> 00:38:24,761
A charade.

514
00:38:27,472 --> 00:38:29,192
A way for governments
who don't give a shit

515
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:31,559
about the war they're
supposed to be fighting...

516
00:38:33,144 --> 00:38:35,188
to go on pretending they're winning it.

517
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:37,732
But it can't be won.

518
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:41,903
It'll never be won.

519
00:38:44,072 --> 00:38:46,658
At least not until people
see it for what it is.

520
00:38:50,078 --> 00:38:51,746
Not until they know the truth.

521
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:23,403
[IN SPANISH] You know what it means
if you go on the record, right?

522
00:39:24,571 --> 00:39:25,864
There'll be a price to pay.

523
00:39:28,825 --> 00:39:30,493
Press the button.

524
00:39:32,912 --> 00:39:34,038
[CLICKS]

525
00:39:34,831 --> 00:39:37,250
Let's start with your
name and occupation.

526
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:46,843
Javier Peña, DEA attaché in Colombia.

527
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:52,557
[PEÑA IN ENGLISH] And
so the truth got out.

528
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:56,728
The news that the Cali cartel had
donated to the president's campaign...

529
00:39:57,228 --> 00:39:59,981
in exchange for virtual immunity...

530
00:40:00,690 --> 00:40:02,650
turned Colombia upside down.

531
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:08,531
And when the highest-ranking DEA agent
in the country went on the record

532
00:40:08,615 --> 00:40:11,659
and said not only did the
United States know about it,

533
00:40:11,743 --> 00:40:13,494
but we allowed it to happen...

534
00:40:14,787 --> 00:40:16,706
they couldn't hide from it anymore.

535
00:40:16,789 --> 00:40:18,666
[REPORTER IN SPANISH]
An exclusive interview.

536
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:21,920
He accuses the country of
being a Narco-Democracy.

537
00:40:22,003 --> 00:40:24,088
He said the country has
fallen into the abyss.

538
00:40:24,464 --> 00:40:27,717
His words have not been well
received by the Colombian people.

539
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:31,679
The public is demanding an
official response from...

540
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:32,805
[TURNS OFF TV]

541
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,910
[IN ENGLISH] You didn't really call
the country that we're guests in

542
00:40:44,943 --> 00:40:46,486
a "Narco-Democracy."

543
00:40:46,569 --> 00:40:47,695
Are you saying it isn't?

544
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:50,156
- The State Department's livid.
- Good.

545
00:40:50,865 --> 00:40:52,450
They're responsible. We all are.

546
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:55,203
Samper is not going anywhere.

547
00:40:56,871 --> 00:41:00,208
Well, at least people know the truth.

548
00:41:06,839 --> 00:41:10,385
I want you gone, Peña.
So do the Colombians.

549
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:11,886
I understand, sir.

550
00:41:19,686 --> 00:41:24,524
You know... any aspirations
you had for your career...

551
00:41:26,192 --> 00:41:28,695
just got dragged behind
the barn and shot.

552
00:41:33,449 --> 00:41:35,785
I resigned from the DEA this morning.

553
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:45,003
[TROPICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

554
00:41:48,965 --> 00:41:51,009
[IN SPANISH] Recordings
that link the president

555
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:53,344
with narcotrafficking have been leaked.

556
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:55,471
[GILBERTO] The reality is
they need five million.

557
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:57,849
- [MIGUEL] Uh-huh.
- We're missing three, see?

558
00:41:57,932 --> 00:41:59,851
- We have it.
- Yes?

559
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,352
Yes, that's done.

560
00:42:01,436 --> 00:42:04,564
This scandal threatens elected
president Ernesto Samper's career

561
00:42:04,647 --> 00:42:08,317
if the authorities confirm his campaign
was funded by narcotrafficking money.

562
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:12,280
[CHANTING] President Samper, the
only solution is your resignation!

563
00:42:12,822 --> 00:42:16,409
Colombians can be certain...

564
00:42:19,829 --> 00:42:25,877
that if they prove any money
transfer of any kind,

565
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:31,007
the deposit would've been
made behind my back.

566
00:42:31,924 --> 00:42:36,345
[PEÑA IN ENGLISH] The Colombians
called the scandal "Proceso 8000."

567
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:40,141
And it set into motion
a series of events...

568
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:44,103
that finally brought the reign of
the Cali godfathers to an end.

569
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:50,318
Chepe Santacruz never did
make it back to New York.

570
00:42:51,903 --> 00:42:54,906
Without the government's guarantee that
their sentences would be minimal...

571
00:42:55,948 --> 00:42:59,535
Chepe decided that prison wasn't
the best place for him to be.

572
00:43:01,079 --> 00:43:03,956
And so... he released himself...

573
00:43:05,541 --> 00:43:08,294
and set out in search of new alliances,

574
00:43:08,377 --> 00:43:11,130
with partners who could help
him rebuild the empire.

575
00:43:11,214 --> 00:43:13,299
You won't believe who he chose.

576
00:43:15,802 --> 00:43:16,928
Don Chepe.

577
00:43:18,846 --> 00:43:20,765
[IN SPANISH] I was happy
to get your call.

578
00:43:22,433 --> 00:43:24,977
[PEÑA IN ENGLISH] Predictably,
it wasn't much of a partnership.

579
00:43:25,728 --> 00:43:29,357
It seems the Castaños expected a
larger contribution to their cause...

580
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:33,778
than Chepe was comfortable making.

581
00:43:34,339 --> 00:43:35,339
[THUMPING]

582
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:37,573
So the alliance died quickly.

583
00:43:38,241 --> 00:43:42,078
And Chepe Santacruz's wild ride...
came to an end.

584
00:43:44,497 --> 00:43:47,542
Pacho Herrera didn't fare
much better staying in jail.

585
00:43:47,875 --> 00:43:50,128
Vendettas in the drug game never end.

586
00:43:50,211 --> 00:43:51,504
[CHEERING]

587
00:43:51,587 --> 00:43:53,422
And Pacho's war on the Salazars...

588
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:56,634
made him some lifelong
North Valley enemies.

589
00:43:58,636 --> 00:44:00,263
[SCREAMS]

590
00:44:01,848 --> 00:44:03,099
Motherfucker!

591
00:44:05,453 --> 00:44:06,453
[CAMERAS CLICKING]

592
00:44:06,477 --> 00:44:09,230
[PEÑA IN ENGLISH] And as for the
Rodríguez-Orejuela brothers,

593
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:13,234
political pressure from the U.S.,
and a disgraced Colombian president

594
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:15,945
who needed to prove he
was tough on narcos...

595
00:44:16,487 --> 00:44:18,627
brought back the only
effective weapon we have

596
00:44:18,652 --> 00:44:22,142
in The War on Drugs: Extradition.

597
00:44:24,579 --> 00:44:28,708
All out of favors and
unlikely to find more,

598
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:32,044
they will spend the rest of
their lives in a U.S. prison.

599
00:44:32,795 --> 00:44:34,297
The good guys didn't do much better.

600
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:35,631
BETRAYAL PAYS

601
00:44:35,715 --> 00:44:39,427
Back in Colombia, Jorge Salcedo
was publicly branded a rat.

602
00:44:39,510 --> 00:44:42,847
The danger that he put himself in to
ensure the success of our operation...

603
00:44:43,306 --> 00:44:45,766
And in the States, despite testimony

604
00:44:45,858 --> 00:44:47,592
that he was instrumental to our efforts

605
00:44:47,655 --> 00:44:50,413
to capture and prosecute
the Cali godfathers,

606
00:44:50,980 --> 00:44:54,233
he still had to plead guilty
to felony conspiracy charges.

607
00:44:56,193 --> 00:44:58,404
And from there, Jorge Salcedo...

608
00:44:59,614 --> 00:45:03,200
the guy who had the most to do with
bringing down the Cali cartel...

609
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:06,746
disappeared into the Federal
Witness Protection Program...

610
00:45:07,705 --> 00:45:09,290
somewhere in the U.S.

611
00:45:11,751 --> 00:45:13,085
A prison of its own.

612
00:45:31,395 --> 00:45:32,688
You knew him, right?

613
00:45:33,105 --> 00:45:34,482
Agent Camarena?

614
00:45:35,441 --> 00:45:38,027
Of him. My first assignment
out of the academy

615
00:45:38,110 --> 00:45:40,905
was a task force that searched
for him in Guadalajara.

616
00:45:42,114 --> 00:45:43,324
It all started there.

617
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:45,868
Before him, we didn't even
know we were in a war.

618
00:45:47,828 --> 00:45:49,705
Another hot one down there for you, huh?

619
00:45:49,789 --> 00:45:51,958
You took down the big
players in Colombia.

620
00:45:52,041 --> 00:45:55,544
Yeah, well... we'll make new ones.

621
00:45:56,337 --> 00:45:58,881
Don't turn a victory
into a defeat, Javier.

622
00:45:58,965 --> 00:46:00,841
The Colombian super-cartels are gone.

623
00:46:00,925 --> 00:46:04,470
And whoever comes next are gonna be
fighting amongst themselves for years.

624
00:46:04,553 --> 00:46:07,473
They're still only going to be a
shadow of what Medellín and Cali were.

625
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:11,435
And now it's time to take the fight to
the real enemy in The War on Drugs.

626
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:13,688
Mexico.

627
00:46:15,439 --> 00:46:17,066
"The real enemy"?

628
00:46:17,692 --> 00:46:18,693
Let me put in some calls.

629
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:20,611
I'll make this bullshit
resignation go away.

630
00:46:24,824 --> 00:46:26,617
What else is a guy like you gonna do?

631
00:46:28,327 --> 00:46:30,246
["XOCHICUICATL" PLAYING]

632
00:46:33,708 --> 00:46:35,459
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

633
00:46:43,009 --> 00:46:45,469
[CHATTER IN SPANISH]

634
00:46:58,357 --> 00:47:01,193
All right, fellas. Let's move.
Keep going.

635
00:47:03,154 --> 00:47:04,594
- [BOAT MOTOR WHIRRING]
- Keep going.

636
00:47:40,649 --> 00:47:42,359
[INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER CAR RADIO]

637
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,073
[GRUNTS]

638
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:49,909
[IN ENGLISH] You helping
me with this or not?

639
00:47:51,077 --> 00:47:52,828
I thought I was getting a partner.

640
00:47:52,912 --> 00:47:54,455
Come on, Pop. Give me that.

641
00:47:55,081 --> 00:47:56,123
[IN SPANISH] Stubborn.

642
00:48:00,628 --> 00:48:03,714
[IN ENGLISH] Stand here for an hour
and you'll count 20 of 'em going by.

643
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:05,674
[IN SPANISH] So...

644
00:48:06,592 --> 00:48:09,595
do you have to fix the fence
every time a storm hits?

645
00:48:11,097 --> 00:48:13,099
Someone has to do it.

646
00:48:13,766 --> 00:48:15,392
That's how life works.

647
00:48:19,855 --> 00:48:21,023
[HORSE SNORTS]

648
00:48:21,107 --> 00:48:22,441
[CLEARS THROAT]

649
00:48:22,525 --> 00:48:24,527
[IN ENGLISH] You thinking
of taking them up on it?

650
00:48:24,944 --> 00:48:25,986
Mexico.

651
00:48:28,405 --> 00:48:29,990
It's different there.

652
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:33,119
- Son, let me tell you...
- Dad.

653
00:48:35,579 --> 00:48:36,872
I've done enough.

654
00:48:39,917 --> 00:48:41,085
I'm through.

655
00:48:49,552 --> 00:48:50,886
Hand me that cutter.

656
00:49:10,114 --> 00:49:12,074
- [GRUNTS]
- [BOAT MOTOR WHIRRING]

657
00:49:13,701 --> 00:49:17,037
